<plot>This short is a follow-up to _Day on Treasure Island, A (1939)_ (qv). That Traveltalk entry showed the Golden Gate International Exposition in the daylight. This film shows the pavilion's lights at night, as well as the decorative fountains and a dancing-light show. Approximately half of the movie's eight minutes are spent inside the Palace of Fine and Decorative Arts. We see paintings by Dutch masters, as well as works by Americans James Chapin and Thomas Hart Benton.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?395847</url></doc>
